3D Orbit & Attitude Visualization Plugin for Grafana
Copyright 2024 Lucas Brémond (Original Work)
Copyright 2025 Ricardo Santos, Instituto Superior Técnico (Derivative Work)

This product is a derivative work based on the Satellite Visualizer Plugin
created by Lucas Brémond, available at:
https://github.com/lucas-bremond/satellite-visualizer

================================================================================

ORIGINAL WORK
================================================================================

Satellite Visualizer Plugin
Copyright 2024 Lucas Brémond
Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

The original plugin provided:
- 3D satellite visualization using CesiumJS
- Grafana panel integration
- Basic trajectory display
- Single satellite support
- Quaternion-based orientation rendering

================================================================================

DERIVATIVE WORK - ENHANCEMENTS AND MODIFICATIONS
================================================================================

The following features and modifications were added to create this derivative work:

1. MULTI-SATELLITE SUPPORT (December 2025)
   - Support for visualizing multiple satellites simultaneously
   - Individual satellite tracking and selection
   - Sidebar menu with satellite list
   - Per-satellite visibility toggles
   - Independent trajectories and time intervals

2. SENSOR VISUALIZATION (December 2025)
   - 3D sensor cone rendering with quaternion-based orientation
   - Ground footprint projection with horizon detection
   - Celestial sphere FOV projection with RA/Dec coordinates
   - Support for unlimited sensors per satellite
   - Configurable FOV, colors, and transparency
   - Adaptive subdivision for smooth horizon curves

3. ATTITUDE VISUALIZATION (December 2025)
   - Body axes display (X, Y, Z) with customizable colors
   - RA/Dec celestial coordinate grid generation
   - Grid labels with Right Ascension and Declination values
   - Master toggle for all attitude-related visualizations
   - Dynamic camera-distance-based scaling for vectors and cones

4. ADVANCED CAMERA CONTROLS (December 2025)
   - Tracking mode with satellite-locked camera
   - Free camera mode with smooth Earth-orbital controls
   - Nadir view button for overhead satellite view
   - Smooth transitions between camera modes
   - Camera position persistence across settings changes

5. DATA PARSING ENHANCEMENTS (December 2025)
   - Extensible JSON data format with meta.custom support
   - Fault-tolerant parsing (missing data doesn't crash plugin)
   - Support for multiple data frames
   - Per-satellite sensor definitions
   - Flexible coordinate system support (Geodetic, ECEF, ECI)

6. USER INTERFACE IMPROVEMENTS (December 2025)
   - Collapsible sidebar with scrollable satellite list
   - Satellite selection and tracking indicators
   - Repositioned Cesium controls for better UX
   - Tooltip-based button labels
   - Configurable UI element visibility

7. TIMELINE PERSISTENCE (December 2025)
   - Fixed timeline reset bug on settings changes
   - Narrowed React useEffect dependencies
   - Separate data-processing and rendering options
   - Maintained animation state across panel updates

8. DOCUMENTATION AND TOOLING (December 2025)
   - Comprehensive README with setup guide
   - ROADMAP for future features
   - Standalone satellite data generator (Keplerian orbits)
   - Pre-generated test data for quick start
   - Development and contribution guidelines

